# Local/dev env files must never be uploaded to Vercel — the project's own
# environment variables are the source of truth in the cloud build. Uploading
# .env / .env.local leaks dev-only keys (e.g. NEXT_PUBLIC_JWT_SECRET, an offline
# dev fallback) into the production build, which the auth-token security guard
# rejects. deploy-v4.sh imports the real env from .env.v4.local into the project.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.production
.env.development
